There you go, tube train commuters.

This man is doing a video stunt that was thrust upon you without any fair warning.

Like it or lump it.

Oh, and don't bother complaining that your sense of relative privacy may be permanently compromised because of someone ELSE'S idea of what might be good for you - you'll have to deal with an army full of intelligent video respondents who think tactfully and considerately of your unspoken, maybe complex personal circumstances as a result.

This video has served to have the opposite effect of what it was promoting - as usual - people appearing NOT to have learned - again - what is, and what isn't, fundamentally beneficial for human beings.

The lesson I picked up from this - watch. your. step. EVERY step.

Why did you make this video in the first place?

Quite clearly not for charity.

Did you do it to make yourself more popular (at the expense of others)?

I think you need to re-examine your philosophy in life. Not joking.
